import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="Penicillin", data=data, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['Penicillin'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Penicillin'].median()))
    ax.axvline(data['Penicillin'].min(), color='g', linestyle='--', label='Min: {:.2f}'.format(data['Penicillin'].min()))
    ax.axvline(data['Penicillin'].max(), color='b', linestyle='--', label='Max: {:.2f}'.format(data['Penicillin'].max()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    ax.set_xlabel('Penicillin')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Penicillin across all bacteria?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.histplot(data=data, x="Streptomycin", color="skyblue", alpha=0.5, label="Streptomycin")
    sns.histplot(data=data, x="Neomycin", color="red", alpha=0.5, label="Neomycin")
    plt.axvline(data['Streptomycin'].mean(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Streptomycin Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['Streptomycin'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['Neomycin'].mean(), color='black', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Neomycin Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['Neomycin'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="Gram_Staining", data=data, palette="Set2")
    ax.set(xlabel='Gram Staining', ylabel='Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Gram_Staining across all bacteria?')
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(f'\n{p.get_height()}', (p.get_x()+0.4, p.get_height()), ha='center', va='top', color='black', size=12)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by=['Genus'])
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="Genus", y="Penicillin", hue="Gram_Staining", data=data, ci=None)
    ax.set_xlabel("Genus")
    ax.set_ylabel("Penicillin Resistance")
    ax.set_title("Which genus of bacteria has the highest and lowest resistance to antibiotics?")
    ax.axhline(y=data['Penicillin'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Penicillin Resistance: {:.2f}'.format(data['Penicillin'].max()))
    ax.axhline(y=data['Penicillin'].min(), color='g', linestyle='--', label='Min Penicillin Resistance: {:.2f}'.format(data['Penicillin'].min()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
